		<div id="post_message_1321756">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Jades</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">For sanctuaries and all that, I would prefer to tell you to wait until sorc data get pushed on test. (Ya I know it's long, even Avair is waiting for it (all is ready) we wait until Silius finish something to patch test server)<br />
<br />
Atm, they are still individual(sanctuaries), Avair isn't against making all of them in 1 sanctuary. <br />
But, here is what I think, that could be very nice if current version isn't totaly what we expected:<br />
<br />
<br />
**I was thinking making 3 kind of... not realy stance or form, but more something like an ability that you active and stay up. It would cost initial mana and then drain our endurance over time (since it's something magical and require us to keep focus on it until we can't anymore)<br />
<br />
1: Sanctuary: Protect every allies in 10m range against all school of magic.<br />
2: Chaos Volley: Release a torrent of energy at your opponent every 5sec (wouldn't affect cooldown of other spell)<br />
3: Anti-Magic Aura: Creat an anti-magic aura of 10m around your offensive target, hurting every mobs in this area every time one of those cast, and raise their casting time by 25% for 5sec.<br />
<br />
So we would have one to protect our allies against magic, one good against single target opponent and one against a single or many mobs, punishing them when one of them cast.<br />
<br />
They would all of them root us in place while it's up and drain our endurance. (only 1 up at the time)**<br />
<br />
I was thinking being able to have more control on our sanctuary, CV (allowing us to use other spells) and Anti-Magic aura.<br />
<br />
Tell me your comments please.<br />
Do you think it would be better this way? or Keep sanctuaries lasting for a fix period, CV direct cast and ... no anti-magic aura, lol</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
This sounds like an interesting and good possibility and could very well be worth implementing.  Perhaps these could be auras and like you have stated would have to choose which one is right for the occasion.  I like your idea of them taking an initial energy cost and slowly draining endurance.  Although I am not sure about changing CV this way I really like your suggestion on the whole.  <br />
<br />
Your idea would have several advantages over what currently exists:  <br />
<br />
It would, without any doubt, add a mouthful of flavor to the sorcerer class and further establish the class's theme.  <br />
<br />
This proposal is very innovative and would solve a few problems at once such as the sometimes too brief sanctuary duration.    <br />
<br />
It would finally implement the anti-magic aura and give some extra diversity and flexibility in how the spell defense works.  <br />
<br />
The plan also would grant the sorc more options for situations especially caster encounters.  <br />
<br />
<br />
Definitely worth strongly considering.  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" />
                  
		</div>
