                  Hmm well thats a hard choice lol.  I really try to take adventuring into account with the new expansion coming out this year and at same time taking account raiding and not knowing jack about PvP really.<br />
<br />
<u><font color="Cyan">Sanctuaries</font></u> <br />
From my perspective sorcerer protect against my spells for their defensive half if I remember the old post from tenofhammer(however it's spelled) when beta was going.  If you want something on par with the druid / cleric / monk / racial DA(barrier) than maybe the all spell school would work instead of doing a rune / DA.  <br />
<br />
It would be nice for adventuring,  many mobs do cast several different spells and an immunity would be nice from all for a short period of time.  I don't know what the plans are for CB though.  Hearing that they are going to revamp mana across the game it would be nice to have a crisis spell if your group is in trouble.  PSI, Druid, Necro all sort or have a crisis &quot;claus&quot;  dump mana,  berries / DA, and FD and rez.  I think this would be a nice balance and fit in rather well to the description of our class.<br />
<br />
On raids it would be nice when your monks all decide to take the same day off.  Any wing for example having two mobs at same time and for some reason you can split them to opposite sides of a room.  One doing ice one doing fire this would be a sure fire way to save the raid just like I listed above for adventuring for the other caster classes.<br />
<br />
I do like the cool down for 10-15 minutes thats on them atm. Putting them all together yes is a great idea and keeping them at same range as what they are now 10m AE.  With the caster group on raids most guilds follow with a WIS / VIT / INT BM in group as a healer your all going to be standing within 10m for heals anyways.   <br />
<br />
<u><font color="Cyan">Chaos Volley</font></u><br />
<br />
I'm a bit confused on the CV (chaos volley).  From a previous post I thought it was said cast three time to achieve the max buff for you or the group.  Could you explain what you meant by <br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				Chaos Volley: Release a torrent of energy at your opponent every 5sec (wouldn't affect cooldown of other spell)
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
From what I read in your last post it doesn't sound like it will be a buff at all more like a dot.  If thats the case it might just be better to have it as a spell you cast once and the dot does so much per 6 seconds for 10 minutes like I think one of the necro dot's do.  Please explain what you meant and correct me.<br />
<br />
<u><font color="Cyan">Anti-Magic Aura</font></u><br />
<br />
The Anti-Magic Aura would rock.  It's basically old school O'kiels Flicker / Flame from EQ spell book, but with a twist.  Hehe I love Vanguard since they taken EQ one step further.  Making it only damage mobs that cast spells on your DT (defensive target) would fall in line with our class description. It would be nice if this was a long duration buff not a 10-30 second buff that has a recast of 10+ minutes.  Maybe like a 5 minute buff so it would be more practical in game play.  As in harder for people to PL (power level).  This is just guessing with wouldn't do some insane about of damage but more a practical damage like 500 or 1k per cast.  I don't know what you really had in idea as for protection spell.  So i just gave my little twist on it.<br />
<br />
<u><font color="Cyan">Stances</font></u><br />
<br />
Hehe had to bug me about the stances and you know how I feel about talking about stances before everything else is fixed.  Well the idea of stance draining endurance or mana is a very nice idea.  I like the extra mechanics / game play it would add to the game.  Having to be in a stance on concentrate requires some much endurance to keep that stance.  I love them theme behind it.  For example some stance on tanks drain endurance per ability in that certain stance.  I believe most cases it's offensive stance that drains the endurance more.  So yes, I do agree that the stance should drain something.  If they didn't then it would be unbalanced to most the other classes i've played that have stance.<br />
<br />
<u><font color="Cyan">Energy Shards</font></u><br />
<br />
I don't know if it was you or some one else but mentioned about shards being tradable.  The idea is nice in theory, but why would there be a need for PSI or druid in groups or on raids then?<br />
<br />
<br />
<u><font color="Cyan">Contact</font></u><br />
What is the best way to contact you in game btw  I really hate forum tag
                  
