                  Yeah, SphereofLight<br />
I'm happy to read all those comments and see that I feel the same.<br />
<br />
If all that get implimented, everything will make sense.<br />
Shocking Grasp: use for direct very big damage, with 60 endurance cost, preventing us to use Sanctuary, CV or Anti-Magic Aura if we are under 60 endurance<br />
<br />
Making it 25m range would only make SG a clone of other spells we already have.<br />
<br />
The way it could deal damage would be cool also if it was something else then direct nuke (we can't impliment % based dmg, but I'm sure we can find another idea)<br />
<br />
The basis of our arsenal is correct, we only need to make a link between all our abilities to give us a reason to cast it at a certain moment and in a certain order.<br />
<br />
We could make a link between each other this way:<br />
each school of magic could have 2 specific effect.<br />
<br />
Arcane: mana feedback and feed CV potential.<br />
Cold: movement debuff and +10% dmg for next fire spell<br />
Fire: Damage over time and +5m range<br />
<br />
That would allow us to:<br />
-use cold spells in combat.<br />
-make special self combo between school of magic.<br />
-not chain cast CV, but still being able to raise his potential with Taqmir and Shocking Grasp<br />
<br />
and with forms and (CV-Sanctuary-Anti-Magic Aura), we would be much more diversified. (more possibilities on how we fight, not only CV.CV.CV)
