	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1322031">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1322031">
                  
                  I think that is a very nice design for Chaos Volley Jades:<br />
<br />
How about Chaos Volley is an effect we place on the foe, that lasts for 20 seconds, 2 second casting time.<br />
<br />
During that time, each arcane spell we cast triggers a small volley on the foe that gets stronger with each cast for up to 6 casts, and at the end of the 20 second duration or final cast, the amount of damage triggered from the volley is delivered in one big hit?<br />
<br />
Like if the volley started at 200, then 400, then 800, then 1200, then 2400, and finally then 4800, then it would trigger at the end for 9800, which is the total of those 6 triggers.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
With this system we would trigger CV on the mob, and then have a full 20 second window in which we would need to cast 6 arcane nukes to get the full  effect of CV, so we would need a minimum of 12 of the 20 seconds devoted to arcane nukes, but we would still have room for error or to mix in flame / ice nukes.<br />
<br />
<br />
I REALLY love the idea of using ice nukes to deal higher damage with fire nukes, that is brilliant. This facilitates spell weaving for optimal performance.<br />
<br />
If they do make ice nukes a facilitator of fire nukes, it would be nice to have a decent ice based damage spell with no or very little reuse. Perhaps simply upping the damage of our snare would be a good option?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
For shocking grasp, i still like my old idea of a short lived dot that requires melee range and channeling, that completely stuns the foe for the duration.<br />
<br />
I was thinking that a 5 duration would be perfect for solo / groups, and for raids it could reduce the attack speed and damage of the foe by 50% for the 5 seconds, so it would be effective while not overpowered.<br />
<br />
Each second its active it would drain endurance, and deliver increasing damage.<br />
<br />
Imagine if it went 250 (instantly), 500 at 1 sec, 750 at 2 sec, 1000 at 3 sec, 1500 at 4 sec, and finally 3000 at 5 sec.<br />
<br />
This would cost all of our endurance, and would probably need a 60 second reuse timer.<br />
<br />
I personally would find this really useful, especially if they tied a de-hate component with it to make it a hate management tool rather than a hate magnet.<br />
<br />
Having a high damage de-hate ability available every minute would defiantly help enable a sorcerer's burst damage in more areas of the game.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
